href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26691">My Stuff</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wulfherehausakliufr>Wulfhere Hausakliufr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/12/01 9:53:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> directly affect tha spell engine</span><hr size=1> Simple really Poe.<br>
<br>
Make ToK induce a long spell RECOVERY time. ToK can be a debuff that will add 6 seconds tha recovery of any spell cast.<br>
<br>
If tha targe be castin then it will recover in an additional 6s. O'erwise tha spell engine will think a spell has just be cast, by tha target, and set recovery time to 6s.<br>
<br>
Ifn tha target be havin an proc/breath attack then it willnae cast any spell afterwards until tha extended recovery time has elapsed.<br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
Alternatively and a bit more interestin tactically... have ToK induce a long spell RECAST time. For any spell being cast by tha target, while tha ToK debuff be on, the recast delay for that spell will be an additional 6-12 seconds.<br>
<br>
This be different in that not all spells be affected, only tha spell just successfully cast. For slow cycle procs/breaths it wil have no effect. For other faster cycling procs/breaths it will stop tha next one. <br>
<br>
For chain cast spells like direct damage and heals it will stop tha target from chain castin for tha next 6-12 seconds. A usefull PvP ability.<br>
<br>
Since tha spell must complete to be impeded by a long recast, it willnae help against Gate.<br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
Either choice should be easy to implement aye Poe?<br>
